<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Timer Setup for Grow Lights for Seedlings</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    The best timer setup is the one that keeps your lights consistent without adding unnecessary complexity.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most home gardeners, the best timer setup for grow lights is a simple timer that runs lights on a consistent daily schedule without requiring manual adjustment.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Seedlings need consistent light more than they need perfectly optimized light. Turning lights on and off manually often leads to irregular schedules, which can affect growth.
  </p>
  <p>
    A timer solves this by keeping your lighting schedule steady every day, without extra effort.
  </p>
