  <h2>Quick Answer: What Timer Setup Works Best?</h2>

  <div class="quickAnswerBox">
    <ul class="plainList">
      <li><strong>Best for most gardeners:</strong> a simple plug-in timer with a fixed daily schedule.</li>
      <li><strong>Best schedule:</strong> consistent on/off cycle every day.</li>
      <li><strong>Best approach:</strong> set it once and leave it alone.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>
    Consistency matters more than fine-tuning the exact number of hours.
  </p>
